    "recap_headline": "University of North Florida",
    "recap_text": "JACKSONVILLE, Fla. -\nNorth Florida Baseball won its second straight series in Atlantic Sun Conference play with a win over FGCU, 7-6, at Harmon Stadium on Saturday.\nWith the win, North Florida improves to 4-1 in ASUN play and moves into first place in the conference's Graphite Division. It marked the second come-from-behind victory for UNF over FGCU in as many games this series.\nSenior catcher\nSantiago Ordonez\nopened the scoring with an RBI double to left-center field to give North Florida a 1-0 lead in the second inning.\nFlorida Gulf Coast tied the score at one in the top of the third frame. Redshirt junior outfielder\nGialdri Gomez\nput North Florida ahead, 2-1, in the bottom-half of the third inning with an RBI single to right field.\nThe Eagles took their largest lead of the game with a 6-2 advantage in the top of the fifth frame.\nFreshman infielder\nJonathan Acosta\ncut North Florida's deficit to 6-3 in the bottom of the fifth inning with his first collegiate home run. Just three at bats later, redshirt junior utility player\nJackson Toberman\nbrought the Ospreys within one run of FGCU with a two-run homer to left field.\nGomez delivered a clutch at bat in the bottom of the seventh inning with a go-ahead two-run home run that brought the score to its eventual final margin.\nSenior right-handed pitcher\nBrandon Adams\nentered in relief for the top of the ninth and notched the save.\nGomez finished the game 2-4 with three RBI and one run. Junior infielder\nMitchell Collins\nand redshirt sophomore outfielder\nSean Benjamin\nalso posted multi-hit performances.\nNORTH FLORIDA 7, FGCU 6\nPitchers of Record\nWin:\nJoseph Dimino\n(1-1)\nLoss:\nHyatt Richardson (3-1)\nLine Scores\nNORTH FLORIDA\n| 7 R, 11 H, 1 E\nFGCU\n| 6 R, 10 H, 0 E\nStatistical Leaders\nNORTH FLORIDA\nGialdri Gomez\n| 2-4, 3 RBI, 1 R\nJackson Toberman\n| 1-4, 2 RBI, 1 R\nMitchell Collins\n| 2-4, 2 R\nSean Benjamin\n| 2-4, 1 R\nCarter White\n| 1-1, 3 BB\nJoseph Dimino\n| 2.0 IP, 0 H, 0 R, 0 ER, 4 K, 1 BB\nFGCU\nEvan Dempsey | 1-3, 1 HR, 1 RBI, 1 R, 1 BB\nUP NEXT\nNorth Florida will remain at Harmon Stadium for Game 3 against Florida Gulf Coast on Sunday, March 22 at 1:05 p.m. ET.",
